mgNumLinks.name: mgNumLinks
mgNumLinks.description: Number of media gateway links (link groups) available in this system.

mgTableEntry.name: mgTableEntry
mgTableEntry.description: Entry holding information about a group of Media Gateway Controllers sharing the same signaling link.

mgLinkName.name: mgLinkName
mgLinkName.description: Name of this media gateway control group.

mgProtocol.name: mgProtocol
mgProtocol.description: Type of the control protocol in use.

mgAdminStatus.name: mgAdminStatus
mgAdminStatus.description: Administrative status for this media gateway control group.

mgOperStatus.name: mgOperStatus
mgOperStatus.description: Current operational status of the signaling link.

mgLastStatusChange.name: mgLastStatusChange
mgLastStatusChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the associated link entered its current operational status. If the current status was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

mgNumInMessages.name: mgNumInMessages
mgNumInMessages.description: Total number of messages received on the link.

mgNumInOctets.name: mgNumInOctets
mgNumInOctets.description: Total number of octets received on the link.

mgNumOutMessages.name: mgNumOutMessages
mgNumOutMessages.description: Total number of messages sent on the link.

mgNumOutOctets.name: mgNumOutOctets
mgNumOutOctets.description: Total number of octets sent on the link.

mgNumErrors.name: mgNumErrors
mgNumErrors.description: Total number of signaling-level errors encountered. Includes, but is not limited to, number of bad messages received, number of failures to sent a message and number of other errors.

mgNumTimerRecovery.name: mgNumTimerRecovery
mgNumTimerRecovery.description: Number of timer recovery events since the statistics was last reset. This reflects all timers.

mgTransportNumLosses.name: mgTransportNumLosses
mgTransportNumLosses.description: Number of times a transport link was lost (excluding switch-over cases).

mgTransportNumSwitchover.name: mgTransportNumSwitchover
mgTransportNumSwitchover.description: Number of times when the signaling was switched over to an alternative link.

mgTransportTotalNumAlarms.name: mgTransportTotalNumAlarms
mgTransportTotalNumAlarms.description: Total number of all alarms issued for the transport layer.

mgTransportLastEvent.name: mgTransportLastEvent
mgTransportLastEvent.description: Last event reported by the transport layer.

mgTransportLastEventTime.name: mgTransportLastEventTime
mgTransportLastEventTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time when the event specified by mgTransportLastEvent occured. If the last event occured prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

mgResetStatistics.name: mgResetStatistics
mgResetStatistics.description: This object can be used to reset all statistics collected for this media gateway link so far. Statistics will be reset when the object is SET to 'reset'. GET from this object always returns 'notApplicable'.

mgLastStatisticsReset.name: mgLastStatisticsReset
mgLastStatisticsReset.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time when the statistics was reset. If the reset occured prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, this object contains a zero value.

mgControllerEntry.name: mgControllerEntry
mgControllerEntry.description: Entry holding information about an individual Media Gateway Controller.

mgControllerIndex.name: mgControllerIndex
mgControllerIndex.description: The index number for this Media Gateway Controller entry. Its value ranges from 1 to the maximum number of controllers per group and identifies which controller the entry is associated with.

mgControllerIPAddress.name: mgControllerIPAddress
mgControllerIPAddress.description: The IP address of the Media Gateway Controller. The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if the entry is invalid.

mgControllerPort.name: mgControllerPort
mgControllerPort.description: TCP port of the Media Gateway Controller. The value 0 is returned if the entry is invalid.

mgControllerOperStatus.name: mgControllerOperStatus
mgControllerOperStatus.description: Status of the transport link to this particular Media Gateway Controller.
